Wondering why two Tojo officers would be at the Omi Headquarters, Kasuga's party has a lengthy battle with Majima, and Saejima jumps in when Majima starts having trouble. Just as Majima and Saejima are about to get serious, Arakawa stops the battle, acknowledging that they are all on the same side and have plans to end Aoki's stranglehold on the yakuza. Saejima is among those defending Daigo and Watase when they announce the disbandment of both the Tojo Clan and Omi Alliance. <b>When [[Kazuma Kiryu]] returns as reinforcements, Saejima is delighted, addressing him as the Dragon of Dojima.</b> {{hr}}
'''''Like a Dragon Gaiden: The Man Who Erased His Name:''''' Saejima joins Majima, Kiryu, [[Yuki Tsuruno|Tsuruno]], Daigo, and Watase in leaving the headquarters, where they are attacked by [[Kosei Shishido]] and Omi loyalists in one last desperate attempt by them to keep the age of yakuza alive. They hold the loyalists at bay while Kiryu fights Shishido, after which they leave the premises. {{hr}}

In the days following, around the time Arakawa is murdered by [[Yosuke Tendo]], attempts to kill Daigo and Watase take place, but Saejima, Majima, and Kiryu successfully defend them.
